Balboa, a Spanish explorer, was the first European to encounter the Pacific Ocean. The first person to circumnavigate the globe was Ferdinand Magellan, who completed the journey in 1522. Sailing around the Cape of Good Hope was achieved by Portuguese explorer Bartolomeu Dias in 1488.
